{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "id": "20-implementation-40-theming-10-global-themes",
  "title": "Global themes",
  "root": "b-global-themes-root",
  "blocks": {
    "b-global-themes-root": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-root",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "children": [
        "b-global-themes-intro-2",
        "b-global-themes-folder-heading-3",
        "b-global-themes-folder-para-4",
        "b-global-themes-manifest-table-5",
        "b-global-themes-example-6",
        "b-global-themes-selection-heading-7",
        "b-global-themes-selection-para-8",
        "b-global-themes-saveas-heading-9",
        "b-global-themes-saveas-rail-10",
        "b-global-themes-saveas-hand-11",
        "b-global-themes-saveas-export-12"
      ]
    },
    "b-global-themes-intro-2": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-intro-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A theme is a folder. While the default theme's identity is being figured out, the picker shows ONLY Default: the rail auto-saves every change (debounced) into the repo's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "themes/default/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "themes/default"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " folder, which overrides the compiled-in fallback — Default IS the living core theme, and selecting it restores the last saved look. Custom themes still live as folders in the repo's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "themes/<id>/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " directory (sibling of "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "docs"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), served by docs-server ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "GET/POST /api/themes",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") and listed in the style rail's Themes section."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-folder-heading-3": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-folder-heading-3",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The folder format"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-folder-para-4": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-folder-para-4",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Each folder holds a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "theme.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " manifest and one "
        },
        {
          "insert": "components/<surface>.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " token file per visual surface (see Component themes). A manifest's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "base",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " names the theme it layers over, so a custom theme overrides only what differs."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-manifest-table-5": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-manifest-table-5",
      "type": "structured-table",
      "props": {
        "columns": [
          "Field",
          "Type",
          "Meaning"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "name",
            "string",
            "Display name in the Themes picker."
          ],
          [
            "base",
            "string (theme id)",
            "Theme to layer over; v1 resolves bases against BUILT-INS only."
          ],
          [
            "dark",
            "boolean",
            "Mode applied when the theme is selected."
          ],
          [
            "fonts",
            "{ body?, heading?, code?, number? }",
            "Font stacks (any string) written to the per-surface font tokens."
          ],
          [
            "railDefaults",
            "partial rail settings",
            "Knob values applied ONCE on selection (a preset ride-along, not a live link)."
          ]
        ],
        "title": "theme.json fields"
      },
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-example-6": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-example-6",
      "type": "code",
      "props": {
        "language": "json"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "// themes/example/theme.json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Example (blue code)\",\n  \"base\": \"default\",\n  \"dark\": false,\n  \"fonts\": { \"code\": \"'Berkeley Mono', ui-monospace, monospace\" }\n}"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-selection-heading-7": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-selection-heading-7",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Selection semantics"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-selection-para-8": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-selection-para-8",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Selecting a theme injects its compiled CSS layer (a light block and a dark block of tier-2 variables) and applies its railDefaults and dark flag once. The style rail stays a personal overlay ON TOP: knob changes afterwards are yours alone and always win over theme values. The selection persists per user ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs-theme-folder-id",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") and re-injects on boot without re-applying railDefaults."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-saveas-heading-9": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-saveas-heading-9",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Creating themes"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-saveas-rail-10": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-saveas-rail-10",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "From the rail: every knob change auto-saves (1.5s debounce) into "
        },
        {
          "insert": "themes/default/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "themes/default"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " via "
        },
        {
          "insert": "POST /api/themes",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — component overrides become real components/*.json files, the rest rides as railDefaults. Named save-as returns when the catalogue reopens."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-saveas-hand-11": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-saveas-hand-11",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "By hand or by agent: create the folder directly — ids are lowercase slugs, content is validated tolerantly on load (unknown fields and keys are ignored, never fatal)."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-global-themes-saveas-export-12": {
      "id": "b-global-themes-saveas-export-12",
      "type": "list-item",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Export/Import theme buttons move just the knob blob (settings JSON + dark flag) between machines — the quick path when a full theme folder is overkill."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    }
  }
}
